  <refnamediv>
    <refname>btkGetScalars</refname>
    <refpurpose>Extract scalars from a biomechanical acquisition</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>btkGetScalars(h)
scalars = btkGetScalars(h)
[scalars, scalarsInfo] = btkGetScalars(h)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>h</term>
        <listitem><para>The handle used to represent an acquisition.</para></listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>Return a structure of scalars.</para>
    <para>Each fieldname in the output argument <literal>scalars</literal> corresponds to a scalar's label.</para>
    <para>The output argument <literal>scalarsInfo</literal> is composed of the following fieldname:
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><literal>frequency</literal>: scalars' frequency ;</listitem>
      <listitem><literal>units</literal>: unit of each scalar.</listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    </para>
    <para>The acquisition is represented by the handle <literal>h</literal>. This handle is obtained  by the use of a btk* function.</para>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Examples</title>
    <programlisting role="example">[scalars, scalarsInfo] = btkGetScalars(h)</programlisting>
  </refsection>
